The paper deals with information extraction, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). It also involves analyzing HTML templates and tree representations, which are common in databases (cs.DB). The proposed method involves annotation and matching of nodes, which are tasks commonly performed in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves large-scale empirical analysis and mathematical quantification, which are tasks commonly performed in machine learning (cs.LG).
